 Like thousands of children, 7-year-old Kyle Carroll takes Ritalin for a diagnosis of attention deficit-hyperactivity disorder, or ADHD.
Researchers examined about 30,000 grade-school children in two districts in southeastern Virginia and found that pupils took drugs for ADHD in school at two to three times the expected rate, according to the study in the American Journal of Public Health.
&UR; ___ &UR; Study shows Ritalin is effective in helping children with ADHD Behavior in children with attention-deficit hyperactivity disorder improves dramatically when they take the controversial drug Ritalin, according to a study.
Attention deficit hyperactivity disorder ADHD is a common psychiatric illness that is believed to affect between 3 and 5 percent of children in the United States.
